{
  "text": "Left ventricular mass (LVM) was calculated from 2D-guided M-mode echocardiographic measurements of the left ventricle. LVM index (LVMI) was calculated by dividing LVM (g) by height (m) exponentiated to the power of 2.7 (gm/m 2.7 ) to correct for effects of age, gender, and overweight status [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Left ventricular hypertrophy (LVH) was defined as LVMI \u03fe95th percentile [CITATION_3] .",
